data-platform â€” Installer Distribution
======================================

The data-platform repository publishes a complete installer tarball that bundles
all runtime components, configuration templates, and operational utilities.

Each release corresponds to a Git tag of the form:

  rel-<version>

Example:
  rel-1.12.0-rc8

------------------------------------------------------------
Release Contents
------------------------------------------------------------

Each release contains:

  data-platform-<version>.tar.gz
    Installer tarball containing the full runtime layout.

  data-platform-<version>.tar.gz.sha256
    SHA-256 checksum for integrity verification.

------------------------------------------------------------
Installer Layout
------------------------------------------------------------

After extraction, the directory structure is:

  data-platform/
    bin/            Startup and utility scripts
    lib/            dp-service, dp-desktop-app, dp-grpc JARs
    config/         Configuration templates
    docker/         Docker deployment examples
    kubernetes/     Kubernetes manifests
    templates/      Supporting templates
    var/
      lock/
      log/

------------------------------------------------------------
Installation
------------------------------------------------------------

1. Download the tarball and checksum from the GitHub Release page.

2. Verify the checksum:

   sha256sum -c data-platform-<version>.tar.gz.sha256

3. Extract the installer:

   tar xzf data-platform-<version>.tar.gz

4. Change into the directory:

   cd data-platform

------------------------------------------------------------
Notes
------------------------------------------------------------

- This installer consumes released artifacts from:
    dp-grpc
    dp-service
    dp-desktop-app

- No compilation is required to run the platform.
- Deployment may be standalone, Docker-based, or Kubernetes-based.
